.TH MOONPI\-KIOSK 8 "2025" "moonpi" "MoonPi System Administration"
.SH NAME
moonpi\-kiosk \- enable or disable kiosk VT\-lock mode for MoonPi
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B moonpi\-kiosk
.I command
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B moonpi\-kiosk
manages kiosk mode for the MoonPi launcher. When kiosk mode is enabled,
virtual terminal switching is locked at the kernel level using the
.B VT_LOCKSWITCH
ioctl, preventing users from escaping to another TTY via keyboard shortcuts
(Ctrl+Alt+Fn) or
.BR chvt (1).
SSH access is unaffected.
.PP
Kiosk mode persists across reboots via a systemd service
.RB ( moonpi\-kiosk.service ).
.B moonpi\-kiosk
must be run as root.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B enable
Lock VT switching immediately, switch the active console to TTY2, and enable
.B moonpi\-kiosk.service
so the lock is re\-engaged automatically on every subsequent boot.
.TP
.B disable
Unlock VT switching immediately, disable
.B moonpi\-kiosk.service
so the lock is not re\-engaged on boot, and redraw the MoonPi menu with
the full set of options restored.
.TP
.B lock
Engage the VT lock ioctl. Used internally by
.BR moonpi\-kiosk.service .
.TP
.B unlock
Release the VT lock ioctl. Used internally by
.BR moonpi\-kiosk.service .
.SH EXAMPLES
Enable kiosk mode:
.PP
.RS
.B sudo moonpi\-kiosk enable
.RE
.PP
Disable kiosk mode:
.PP
.RS
.B sudo moonpi\-kiosk disable
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR moonpi (1),
.BR moonpi\-safe (1),
.BR chvt (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
